revision.text:
'''Bülent Hass Dellal''' {{post-nominals|country=AUS|AO}} is a director and the chairman of the [[Special Broadcasting Service]] (SBS) in Australia.<ref name="SBS">{{cite web|author=SBS|title=Bülent Hass Dellal|url=http://www.sbs.com.au/aboutus/board-of-directors/director/id/140/h/Bulent-Hass-Dellal|accessdate=2012-09-12}}</ref>

==Life and career==
Dellal was born in [[Melbourne]], [[Australia]], to [[Turkish Cypriot]] parents,<ref name="Gobbo 2010 loc=205">{{Harvnb|Gobbo|2010|loc=205}}.</ref><ref name="ECCV">{{cite web|author=Ethnic Communities Council of Victoria|title=20 January 2011—Victoria’s 2011 Australia Day Ambassadors feature champions of cultural diversity|url=http://eccv.org.au/community/media-releases/20-january-2011-victorias-2011-australia-day-ambassadors-feature-champions-of-cultural-diversity/|accessdate=2012-09-12}}</ref> and is the eldest of three children.<ref name="Hüssein 2007 loc=154">{{Harvnb|Hüssein|2007|loc=154}}.</ref> His great-grandfather was the last [[Ottoman Empire|Ottoman]] [[mufti]] of [[Cyprus]].<ref name="TodaysZaman">{{cite web|author=Today's Zaman|title=Australia’s Turkish delight|url=http://www.todayszaman.com/newsDetail_getNewsById.action;jsessionid=A19DA82F07D75286F29CBD4D78E43599?pageNo=1312&category=&dt=2010&newsId=199931&columnistId=0|accessdate=2012-09-12}}</ref> Dellal's early childhood was spent in [[Glenroy, Victoria|Glenroy]], where he attended primary school. Dellal spent his after school hours and weekends helping his father, Hasan, with the general store they owned in Glenroy. His father devoted his spare time towards assisting Turkish Cypriot immigrants who settled in Australia and helped form the [[Cyprus Turkish Association]]. He also founded the Cyprus Turkish Islamic Society, and was responsible for managing the construction of the [[Sunshine Mosque]].<ref name="Hüssein 2007 loc=154"/> Although the Turkish culture was a strong presence within his household, Dellal and his siblings found it difficult to speak the language, preferring instead to speak in [[English language|English]]. His father decided to move the family to [[Turkey]], so that the children would gain a stronger sense of their culture.<ref name="Hüssein 2007 loc=155">{{Harvnb|Hüssein|2007|loc=155}}.</ref> In 1962, at the age of 10, Dellal's family sold their assets and moved to [[Ankara]], Turkey but returned to Australia, in 1965, where he spent his secondary school years.<ref name="Hüssein 2007 loc=156-57">{{Harvnb|Hüssein|2007|loc=156-57}}.</ref> Dellal studied at [[Merrilands College|Merrilands Secondary College]] and then at the Melba Conservatory in Richmond. Once he finished his studies, he became a teacher at a Catholic girl's college. In 1989, Dellal became the founding executive of the Australian Multicultural Foundation (AMF). His efforts were recognised in 1997 when he was awarded the Medal of the [[Order of Australia]] by [[Queen Elizabeth II]] for his support of multicultural affairs, the arts and the community. In 2003 he was awarded the [[Centenary of Federation Medal]] for his contribution to Australian society.<ref name="Hüssein 2007 loc=159">{{Harvnb|Hüssein|2007|loc=159}}.</ref>

