{{Infobox organization | name = Institute of Workplace and Facilities Management | image = | image_border = | size = <!-- default 200px --> | alt = <!-- alt text; see [[WP:ALT]] --> | caption = | map = <!-- optional --> | msize = <!-- map size, optional, default 250px --> | malt = <!-- map alt text --> | mcaption = <!-- optional --> | map2 = | abbreviation = | motto = | formation = 1993 ({{years ago|1993}} years ago) as BIFM<ref name="About">{{cite web |title=About us |url=https://www.bifm.org.uk/bifm/about |website=BIFM |accessdate=8 June 2018}}</ref> <!--{{Start year and years {{Start date and years ago|YYYY|MM|DD}}--> | type = [[Professional association]] | status = <!-- ad hoc, treaty, foundation, etc --> | purpose = [[Facilities management]]<!-- focus as e.g. humanitarian, peacekeeping, etc --> | headquarters = [[Bishop's Stortford]], [[Hertfordshire]], [[England]], United Kingdom | location = | coords = <!-- Coordinates of location using a coordinates template --> | region_served = | membership = 17,000+ (at June 2018)<ref name="FMJ-31May2018"/> | language = <!-- official languages --> | general = <!-- Secretary General --> | leader_title = <!-- position title for the leader of the org --> | leader_name = <!-- name of leader --> | leader_title2 = | leader_name2 = | leader_title3 = | leader_name3 = | leader_title4 = | leader_name4 = | key_people = | main_organ = <!-- gral. assembly, board of directors, etc --> | parent_organization = <!-- if one --> | affiliations = [[Construction Industry Council]] | budget = | num_staff = | website = [http://www.iwfm.org.uk www.iwfm.org.uk] }}
The '''Institute of Workplace and Facilities Management''' (IWFM; formerly the '''British Institute of Facilities Management''', BIFM) is a [[United Kingdom]]-based [[professional association]] for the [[facility management|facilities management]] sector.
==History== BIFM was formed in 1993<ref name="About"/> to promote the development of facilities management as a critical, professional and strategic business discipline.<ref name="Atkin">{{cite book |last1=Atkin |first1=Brian |last2=Brooks |first2=Adrian |title=Total Facilities Management |date=2009 |publisher=John Wiley & Sons |location=London |isbn=9781444316131 |page=4 |edition=3rd }}</ref> In June 2018 the BIFM had around 17,000 individual members.<ref name="FMJ-31May2018"/>
BIFM was a founding member of the [[Global Facility Management Association (Global FM)]],<ref>https://globalfm.org/home-3/member-organisation/</ref> and a full member of the [[Construction Industry Council]].<ref name="CICmem">{{cite web |title=CIC Members |url=http://cic.org.uk/about-us/cic-members.php |website=Construction Industry Council |accessdate=8 June 2018}}</ref>
In May 2018, the BIFM proposed changing its name to the Institute of Workplace and Facilities Management and attaining [[Royal charter|chartered]] body status.<ref name="FMJ-31May2018">{{cite news |last1=OBeirne |first1=Sarah |title=FM Clinic: Debate on BIFM’s proposed rebrand and application for chartered body status |url=http://www.fmj.co.uk/fm-clinic-debate-on-bifms-proposed-rebrand-and-application-for-chartered-body-status/ |accessdate=8 June 2018 |work=Facilities Management Journal |date=31 May 2018}}</ref><ref name="FMW-4Jun2018">{{cite news |title=Working up a theme |url=http://www.fm-world.co.uk/news/news-analysis/working-up-a-theme/ |accessdate=8 June 2018 |work=FM World |date=4 June 2018}}</ref> The name change was implemented in November 2018.<ref name="Obeirne-16Nov2018">{{cite news |last1=Obeirne |first1=Sarah |title=BIFM makes big switch to IWFM with a new ten point plan |url=https://www.fmj.co.uk/bifm-makes-big-switch-to-iwfm-with-a-new-ten-point-plan/ |accessdate=29 November 2018 |work=Facilities Management Journal |date=16 November 2018}}</ref>
