{{Infobox football biography |name = Jan Louwers |image = |caption = |fullname = |birth_date = {{birth date|1930|7|3|df=y}} |birth_place = [[Eindhoven]], Netherlands |death_date = {{death date and age|2012|11|1|1930|7|3|df=y}} |death_place = [[Eindhoven]], Netherlands |height = |position = |youthyears1 = |youthclubs1 = |years1 = 1949–1960 |clubs1 = [[FC Eindhoven]] |caps1 = |goals1 = |years2 = 1960–1963 |clubs2 = [[PSV Eindhoven|PSV]] |caps2 = |goals2 = |years3 = 1963–1966 |clubs3 = [[Roda JC Kerkrade|Roda JC]] |caps3 = |goals3 = |years4 = 1966–1967 |clubs4 = [[FC Eindhoven]] |caps4 = |goals4 = |totalcaps = |totalgoals = }} '''Jan Louwers''' (3 July 1930 – 1 November 2012) was a Dutch professional [[association football|footballer]] and millionaire businessman.
==Career== Louwers played football for [[FC Eindhoven]], [[PSV Eindhoven|PSV]] and [[Roda JC Kerkrade|Roda JC]].<ref name = "ed.nl">{{cite web|url=http://www.ed.nl/sport/fce/11965713/Eindhoven-icoon-Louwers-overleden.ece|title=Eindhovens voetbalicoon Jan Louwers (82) overleden|date=1 November 2012|language=Dutch|publisher=ed.nl}}</ref> The [[Jan Louwers Stadion]] is named after him.<ref name = "ed.nl"/>
After retiring in 1967 he became a wholesaler; in 1988 his company had a turnover of €80 million.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eindhoven-in-beeld.nl/picture/number1416.asp|title=Jan Louwers, voetballer, ondernemer, miljoenair|date=28 September 2005|language=Dutch|publisher=eindhoven-in-beeld.nl}}</ref>
