'''Lorenzo Borghese''' ({{lang-it|Don Lorenzo dei Principi Borghes}}; born June 9, 1972) is an Italian-American businessman, television personality, and member of the  [[House of Borghese|Borghese family]]. Besides being a cosmetics entrepreneur and animal advocate, Borghese was a bachelor on the ninth season of [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]]'s ''[[The Bachelor (U.S. TV series)|The Bachelor]]''.

He is the son of Prince Francesco Marco Luigi Costanzo Borghese (born 1938) and his American wife, Amanda Leigh, daughter of [[Douglas Leigh]]. Borghese's paternal grandmother was [[Princess Marcella Borghese]], who founded the ''Borghese'' cosmetics line in 1958.<ref>{{cite web|title=Why European Royalty and Aristocrats are flocking to New York|url=http://gotham-magazine.com/living/articles/why-european-royalty-and-aristocrats-are-flocking-to-new-york}}</ref>

==Early life and education==
Borghese was born on June 9, 1972, in Milan, Italy. Borghese's parents, Francesco and Amanda Borghese, have lived in [[Short Hills, New Jersey]] since 1979.<ref name=usweekly>[http://www.usmagazine.com/entertainment/news/the-bachelor-less-italian-and-princey-than-originally-thought-2006310 The Bachelor Less Italian and Princey Than Originally Thought], ''Us Weekly'', October 3, 2006. Accessed July 26, 2014.</ref> He holds dual U.S./Italian citizenship. Raised in Short Hills, he attended elementary school there.<ref name=usweekly/> He then graduated from [[Pomfret School]] in [[Pomfret, Connecticut]], in 1991.<ref>[https://www.pomfretschool.org/podium/default.aspx?t=52302&pg=120 Pomfret School]  {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131005120953/https://www.pomfretschool.org/podium/default.aspx?t=52302&pg=120 |date=October 5, 2013 }}</ref> In 1995, he graduated from [[Rollins College]] in [[Winter Park, Florida]], where he was initiated into the [[Phi Delta Theta]] fraternity.<ref>[https://wayback.archive-it.org/all/20131216104728/http://www.rollins.edu/125/pointsofpride/4.html Rollins] </ref> 

He earned an MBA degree from the [[Fordham Graduate School of Business]] in 2001.<ref>[http://www.bnet.fordham.edu/enews/faculty/fall2009/kudoscorneralumni.html Fordham University] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131004213352/http://www.bnet.fordham.edu/enews/faculty/fall2009/kudoscorneralumni.html |date=2013-10-04 }} {{failed verification|date=September 2015}}</ref>

==Business and philanthropy==
Borghese resides in New York City. He initiated the Royal Treatment line of products,<ref>[http://www.royalpetclub.com/Our-heritage.html Royal Pet Club - Our heritage]</ref> a bath, body and skin care line for pets, using organic ingredients and fragrance oils from Italy, which can be found in hundreds of stores nationwide and on the television station [[Home Shopping Network|HSN]]. He is a managing partner in LB2, LLC, a private-label Italian cosmetics company that sells numerous brands to major department stores and direct retail outlets.<ref>{{cite journal|title=Marcella Borghese; Princess, 90, Began a Line of Cosmetics|journal=The New York Times|date=February 8, 2002|page=21}}</ref> In 2014, he launched Rumgolf,<ref>[http://rumgolf.com RumGolf]</ref>

He has been honored with numerous awards for his animal advocacy work, including the Animal Advocacy Award presented to him in 2014 by Bideawee and the Pet Hero Humanitarian Award presented to him by the Pet Philanthropy Circle. Lorenzo was a bachelor contestant in an animal rescue fundraiser called Barks, Babes, and Brews in 2015 hosted by [[Salty Dog Paddle]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.palmbeachpost.com/entertainment/date-hottie-have-some-drinks-save-dog/oaPN88luEvUjCFTjwzkQ2M/|title=Date a hottie, have some drinks, save a dog!|work=palmbeachpost|access-date=2018-10-03}}</ref>

==Reality television and author==
In the fall of 2006, Borghese starred in the ninth season of ABC's popular reality show ''[[The Bachelor (U.S. TV series)|The Bachelor]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.buddytv.com/articles/the-bachelor/another-breakup-for-the-bachel-4727.aspx |title=Another Breakup for The Bachelor's Lorenzo Borghese|publisher=Buddytv.com|date=2007-03-07|accessdate=2012-09-21}}</ref>

In the summer of 2009, Borghese announced he would be searching for his "princess" on a web reality show titled ''[[America's Next Princess]]''. The show was to coincide with the launch of Royal Pet Club,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.royalpetclub.com|title=Organic Dog Shampoo &#124; Natural Dog Shampoo &#124; Pet Supplies for Dogs|publisher=Royalpetclub.com|accessdate=2012-09-21}}</ref> an online shopping destination for his Royal Treatment pet products.<ref>[http://www.officialwire.com/main.php?action=posted_news&rid=11187&catid=126 Prince Lorenzo Borghese Searches for his Princess on "America's Next Princess"]</ref> However, when the show debuted online on August 17, 2009, the series was actually revealed to be a spoof of celebrities and [[reality TV]] shows.<ref>[https://finance.yahoo.com/news/Americas-Next-Top-Dog-The-bw-1237894278.html?x=0&.v=1 "America's Next Top Dog - The Princess" Reveals Big Twist in New Web Series with a Cast Made up Entirely of Dogs]</ref>

In August/September 2012, he appeared on the 10th season of ''[[Celebrity Big Brother 10|Celebrity Big Brother UK]]'' and was evicted from the house on Day 22, ultimately finishing in 8th place.<ref>[http://www.digitalspy.com/british-tv/s150/celebrity-big-brother/news/a404095/julie-goodyear-prince-lorenzo-evicted-from-celebrity-big-brother.html#~pd34wLjR3VSkhI "Julie Goodyear, Prince Lorenzo evicted from Celebrity Big Brother"] (Sep 5, 2012) Digital Spy</ref>

==Titles==
Although he is often attributed the title of Prince, the title is actually his father's who is currently the 17th Prince of Sant'Angelo and San Polo.<ref>http://www.genmarenostrum.com/pagine-lettere/letterab/Borghese/BORGHESE%203.htm</ref>

